<project name="BJCMS - Sound Visualizer" app="Snap! 6, https://snap.berkeley.edu" version="1"><notes></notes><thumbnail>data:image/png;base64,</thumbnail><stage name="Stage" width="480" height="360" costume="0" color="255,255,255,1" tempo="60" threadsafe="false" penlog="false" volume="100" pan="0" lines="round" ternary="false" hyperops="true" codify="false" inheritance="true" sublistIDs="false" scheduled="false" id="1"><pentrails>data:image/png;base64,</pentrails><costumes><list struct="atomic" id="2"></list></costumes><sounds><list struct="atomic" id="3"></list></sounds><variables></variables><blocks></blocks><scripts></scripts><sprites><sprite name="Sprite" idx="1" x="-240" y="0" heading="90" scale="1" volume="100" pan="0" rotation="1" draggable="true" costume="0" color="80,80,80,1" pen="tip" id="8"><costumes><list struct="atomic" id="9"></list></costumes><sounds><list struct="atomic" id="10"></list></sounds><blocks></blocks><variables></variables><scripts><script x="13.333333333333334" y="110.33333333333366"><block s="reportAudio"><l><option>volume</option></l><comment w="288.6666666666667" collapsed="true">reports an instantaneous microphone loudness value</comment></block></script><script x="13.333333333333334" y="140.33333333333334"><block s="reportAudio"><l><option>samples</option></l><comment w="205.33333333333334" collapsed="false">reports frequency values (between -1 and 1) across a small period of time</comment></block></script><script x="13.333333333333334" y="204.33333333333334"><block s="reportAudio"><l><option>resolution</option></l><comment w="136" collapsed="false">reports the number of values in a microphone output list</comment></block></script><script x="13.333333333333334" y="329.33333333333303"><block s="doForEach"><l>sample</l><block s="reportAudio"><l><option>samples</option></l></block><script><block s="gotoXY"><block s="reportSum"><block s="xPosition"></block><block var="step"/></block><block s="reportProduct"><block var="sample"/><l>150</l></block></block></script></block></script><script x="13.333333333333334" y="657.5555555555562"><block s="doForever"><script><block s="doWarp"><script><block s="gotoXY"><l>-240</l><l>0</l></block><block s="clear"></block><block s="doDeclareVariables"><list><l>step</l></list></block><block s="doSetVar"><l>step</l><block s="reportQuotient"><block s="reportAttributeOf"><l><option>width</option></l><l>Stage</l></block><block s="reportAudio"><l><option>resolution</option></l></block></block></block><block s="down"></block><block s="doForEach"><l>sample</l><block s="reportAudio"><l><option>samples</option></l></block><script><block s="gotoXY"><block s="reportSum"><block s="xPosition"></block><block var="step"/></block><block s="reportProduct"><block var="sample"/><l>150</l></block></block></script></block></script></block></script></block></script><script x="13.333333333333334" y="1245.5555555555557"><block s="reportAudio"><l><option>spectrum</option></l><comment w="205.33333333333334" collapsed="false">reports instantaneous microphone intensity values across a range of frequencies</comment></block></script><script x="13.333333333333334" y="1394.5555555555559"><block s="doStopThis"><l><option>all</option></l></block></script><script x="13.333333333333334" y="1429.2222222222226"><block s="doForever"><script><block s="doWarp"><script><block s="gotoXY"><l>-240</l><l>0</l></block><block s="clear"></block><block s="doDeclareVariables"><list><l>step</l></list></block><block s="doSetVar"><l>step</l><block s="reportQuotient"><block s="reportAttributeOf"><l><option>width</option></l><l>Stage</l></block><block s="reportAudio"><l><option>resolution</option></l></block></block></block><block s="down"></block><block s="doForEach"><l>frequency</l><block s="reportAudio"><l><option>spectrum</option></l><comment w="90" collapsed="false">Now we are looking at the frequency spectrum. The intensities won&apos;t be negative, but they might be in the hundreds or higher, so we shift down.</comment></block><script><block s="gotoXY"><block s="reportSum"><block s="xPosition"></block><block var="step"/></block><block s="reportDifference"><block var="frequency"/><l>150</l></block></block></script></block></script></block></script></block></script><script x="13.333333333333334" y="1984.0000000000007"><block s="doStopThis"><l><option>all</option></l></block></script><script x="13.333333333333334" y="2018.6666666666672"><block s="doForever"><script><block s="doIfElse"><block var="toggle"/><script><custom-block s="show samples"></custom-block></script><script><custom-block s="show frequencies"></custom-block></script></block></script><comment w="344.6666666666667" collapsed="false">The forever block has been removed from the previous scripts before they were added to the SHOW SAMPLES and SHOW FREQUENCIES blocks, so the computer will run one of these forever, and which one will depend on the toggle, which can be changed with a keypress because of the script below.&#xD;&#xD;After stopping all other scripts, turn this script on, then press space, and make some noise!</comment></block></script><script x="13.333333333333334" y="2140.4444444444453"><block s="receiveKey"><l><option>space</option></l></block><block s="doSetVar"><l>toggle</l><block s="reportNot"><block var="toggle"/></block></block></script><comment x="13.333333333333334" y="13.333333333333334" w="427.3333333333333" collapsed="false">This oscilloscope project shows the frequency of the microphone.&#xD;&#xD;Make some noise! Click each of these reporters and read the comment to see what it reports. &#xD;&#xD;(You can also right-click any block and choose &quot;help...&quot; to learn more about how it works.)</comment><comment x="13.333333333333334" y="268.3333333333333" w="366.6666666666667" collapsed="false">This is the core of the oscilloscope code. It will not run on it&apos;s own, but take time to understand how it works. (Details are below, but try to understand it yourself first.)</comment><comment x="13.333333333333334" y="402.5555555555558" w="388" collapsed="false">For each microphone sample (each frequency value), the sprite (the arrowhead object on the stage) will:&#xD;1) increment (increase) horizontally by some pre-specified step and&#xD;2) go to a scaled up multiple of the microphone sample value. (Sample values are from -1 to 1, so the scaled values are from -150 to 150.)</comment><comment x="13.333333333333334" y="499.5555555555561" w="400" collapsed="false">OPTIONAL: To see the dimensions of the stage, click the &quot;Stage&quot; icon in the lower right corner of the Snap! window, select &quot;Backgrounds...&quot; from the Snap! file menu, choose the &quot;XY Grid&quot; and click &quot;Import,&quot; and then return to this code, by clicking the &quot;Sprite&quot; icon in the lower right corner and selecting the &quot;Scripts&quot; tab at the top of this scripting area. (Instructions like this will be in the Google doc for students; this is just a preview.) :)</comment><comment x="13.333333333333334" y="596.5555555555561" w="348.6666666666667" collapsed="false">Here is the code for oscilloscope. Click it to see what it does, and make some noise! Try to understand the basic idea on your own. There are details below.</comment><comment x="13.333333333333334" y="894.5555555555557" w="426" collapsed="false">What happens? &#xD;&#xD;The sprite starts out at the right-hand center of the stage (-240,0). The stage is cleared from all previous pen drawings (note that the stage background remains if you set it do the XY Grid). A script variable STEP is created and set to the width of the stage divided by the number of values in the microphone sample set (so that the sprite moves horizontally across the whole stage as it goes through the list of samples. The sprite&apos;s pen is put down. Then, for each sample in the set of microphone samples, the sprite moves to the next x position horizontally and to the scaled up version of the current frequency sample vertically, and it does all this forever, thus creating an oscilloscope!&#xD;&#xD;(This code is wrapped in a WARP block—think time-warp—so that Snap! draws quickly.) </comment><comment x="13.333333333333334" y="1075.5555555555557" w="372.6666666666667" collapsed="false">With a few small edits, this same code can become a frequency analyzer. &#xD;&#xD;For the oscilloscope, the horizontal access showed time and the vertical showed intensity (frequency appeared only in the period of—the spacing between—the waves). In the frequency analyzer, the horizontal access will show intensity and the vertical will show frequency.</comment><comment x="13.333333333333334" y="1184.5555555555557" w="240" collapsed="false">Click the following block when you aren&apos;t making noise, and then make some noise and click it again.</comment><comment x="13.333333333333334" y="1309.5555555555559" w="460" collapsed="false">Be sure to turn off the oscilloscope above before turning on the frequency analyzer below.&#xD;&#xD;You can stop that script by going back and clicking it again, or by stopping all scripts by clicking the red stop sign in the upper right corner or by clicking the STOP ALL block.</comment><comment x="13.333333333333334" y="1727.0000000000007" w="426" collapsed="false">What happens now? &#xD;&#xD;The setup is the same, but now for each frequency in the microphone spectrum, the sprite moves to the x position corresponding to that frequency and to the y position corresponding to the intensity of that frequency.</comment><comment x="13.333333333333334" y="1824.0000000000007" w="464" collapsed="false">Ideas to review:&#xD;&#xD;What does each visualizer show? What data is being displayed and what information is plotted on each axis?&#xD;&#xD;What parts of the code for each visualizer is the same? Why? What does that code do?&#xD;&#xD;What parts of the code differ? Why?</comment><comment x="13.333333333333334" y="1957.0000000000007" w="472.6666666666667" collapsed="true">We can also wrap these scripts inside abstractions and create code to toggle between them.</comment></scripts></sprite><watcher var="toggle" style="normal" x="10" y="10" color="243,118,29"/></sprites></stage><hidden>getPosition doDefineBlock doDeleteBlock doSetBlockAttribute reportBlockAttribute reportThisContext reportMousePosition reportCrossproduct </hidden><headers></headers><code></code><blocks><block-definition s="show samples" type="command" category="sound"><header></header><code></code><translations></translations><inputs></inputs><script><block s="doWarp"><script><block s="gotoXY"><l>-240</l><l>0</l></block><block s="clear"></block><block s="doDeclareVariables"><list><l>step</l></list></block><block s="doSetVar"><l>step</l><block s="reportQuotient"><block s="reportAttributeOf"><l><option>width</option></l><l>Stage</l></block><block s="reportAudio"><l><option>resolution</option></l></block></block></block><block s="down"></block><block s="doForEach"><l>sample</l><block s="reportAudio"><l><option>samples</option></l></block><script><block s="gotoXY"><block s="reportSum"><block s="xPosition"></block><block var="step"/></block><block s="reportProduct"><block var="sample"/><l>150</l></block></block></script></block></script></block></script></block-definition><block-definition s="show frequencies" type="command" category="sound"><header></header><code></code><translations></translations><inputs></inputs><script><block s="doWarp"><script><block s="gotoXY"><l>-240</l><l>0</l></block><block s="clear"></block><block s="doDeclareVariables"><list><l>step</l></list></block><block s="doSetVar"><l>step</l><block s="reportQuotient"><block s="reportAttributeOf"><l><option>width</option></l><l>Stage</l></block><block s="reportAudio"><l><option>resolution</option></l></block></block></block><block s="down"></block><block s="doForEach"><l>frequency</l><block s="reportAudio"><l><option>spectrum</option></l></block><script><block s="gotoXY"><block s="reportSum"><block s="xPosition"></block><block var="step"/></block><block s="reportDifference"><block var="frequency"/><l>150</l></block></block></script></block></script></block></script></block-definition></blocks><variables><variable name="toggle"><bool>false</bool></variable></variables></project>
